quran[53]{c,v,t}:
  37,22,"But We shall say, \"Assemble those who did wrong together with their associates and what they worshipped"
  37,23,"besides God, and lead them to the path of the Fire"
  37,24,and stop them there for questioning
  37,25,But what is the matter with you that you cannot help one another
  37,26,"indeed, on that Day they will surrender themselves"
  37,27,"They will turn upon one another, and question one another"
  37,28,"They will say, \"You used to come at us from the right"
  37,29,"They will say, \"No! It was you who would not believe"
  37,30,we had no power over you; but you yourselves were a rebellious people
  37,31,"But now our Lord's word has come true against us: truly, we are bound to taste [the punishment]"
  37,32,We led you astray as we were ourselves astray
  37,33,On that Day they will all share the punishment
  37,34,that is how We deal with evil-doers
  37,35,"When they were told, \"There is no deity but God,\" they turned away with disdain"
  37,36,"and replied, \"Shall we then give up our deities at the bidding of a mad poet"
  37,37,"Surely, he has brought the truth, confirming those who were sent before"
  37,38,you shall surely taste the painful punishment
  37,39,and be rewarded only according to your deeds
  37,40,But the chosen servants of God
  37,41,shall have a known provision
  37,42,fruits of various kinds; and they shall be honoured
  37,43,in the Gardens of Bliss
  37,44,"seated on couches, facing one another"
  37,45,A drink will be passed round among them from a flowing spring
  37,46,white and delicious to those who drink it
  37,47,causing no headiness or intoxication
  37,48,"With them will be spouses, modest of gaze and beautiful of eye"
  37,49,like closely guarded pearls
  37,50,They will turn to one another with questions
  37,51,"one of them will say, \"I had a friend"
  37,52,"who used to ask, 'Do you really believe that"
  37,53,"after we die and become dust and bones, we shall be brought to judgement"
  37,54,"Then he will say, \"Shall we look for him"
  37,55,Then he will look and see him in the midst of the Fire
  37,56,"He will say, \"By God! You almost brought me to ruin"
  37,57,"If it had not been for the blessing of my Lord, I would also have been taken to Hell"
  37,58,"Then he will say [to his blessed companions], \"Are we not going to die"
  37,59,except for our first death? Are we not going to be punished
  37,60,"Truly, this is a great victory"
  37,61,It is for the like of this that all should strive
  37,62,Is that better by way of hospitality or the Zaqqum tree
  37,63,which We have made as a test for the wrongdoers
  37,64,For it is a tree that springs out of the bottom of Hellfire
  37,65,and its fruits are like devils' heads
  37,66,They will eat from it and fill their bellies with it
  37,67,then in addition to it they shall have a draught of boiling water to drink
  37,68,then surely they shall return to Hell
  37,69,They found their fathers had gone astray
  37,70,so they are rushing to follow in their footsteps
  37,71,And assuredly many of the ancients went astray before them
  37,72,though We had sent warners among them
  37,73,See how those who were warned met their end
  37,74,Not so the chosen servants of God